\section{Fabrication}
Starting with bulk wafers oxidized with 3µm thickness, an hydrogenated amorphous silicon layer of 253nm was deposited by Plasma-enhanced chemical vapor deposition (PECVD) at 350\textcelsius. Waveguides were formed using DUV lithography and HBr Reactive-ion etching, then covered with $1.5\mu m$ thick silica.

 On the other hand, silicon‑-on‑-insulator (SOI) waveguides were also fabricated for comparison. These were processed from SOI wafers with 220nm Silicon thickness, patterned with deep-UV lithography and covered with silica after the etching process. Their dimensions were 445x220 for transverse-electric (TE) polarization and 485x220 for transverse-magnetic (TM) polarization. Total length was 20mm for the amorphous Silicon waveguide and 25mm for the SOI waveguides.


%Then using DUV lithography and HBr RIE etching waveguides were formed and covered with $1.5\mu m$ thick silica.

